message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in the Czech Republic in the past 20 years is the country's accession to the European Union (EU) on May 1, 2004. This marked a major milestone in the country's history and led to various political, economic, and social changes. The Czech Republic's EU membership enabled it to benefit from the single market, freedom of movement, and various funding programs. It also played a role in shaping the country's direction and increasing its integration into the broader European community.
